title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. synopsis: Lille have won just one of their last 13 home Ligue 1 games against Paris SG, a 5-1 victory on 14 April 2019, which remains Paris Saint-Germain's biggest away defeat in the top-flight in the 21st century. Lille have lost their last two Ligue 1 matches and could suffer three consecutive defeats in the competition for the first time since December 2019-January 2020. West Ham United are looking to become only the second side to win three successive Premier League away games against Arsenal, after Manchester City, who won six on the bounce from March 2018 to February 2023.

synopsis: Everton have lost just one of their last 21 Premier League meetings with Crystal Palace, a 1-3 defeat in December 2021. Indeed, among all sides they have faced 20+ times in the competition, their points-per-game rate of 1.81 against the Eagles is bettered only against West Brom. Crystal Palace are winless in each of their last 10 Premier League away games against Everton  since a 3-2 victory in September 2014 under Neil Warnock.

title: Chelsea vs Benfica - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Benfica - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
synopsis: Chelsea have won all four of their competitive meetings with Benfica, with the most recent of those coming earlier this year at the FIFA Club World Cup. This will be the first meeting between Chelsea and Benfica in the group/league phase of a competition, with the previous four all having come in the knockout stages: UEFA Champions League quarter-finals in 2011-12, UEFA Europa League final in 2012-13 and the FIFA Club World Cup last 16 earlier this year.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Leeds United vs Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Leeds United vs Tottenham Hotspur - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Leeds United have lost nine of their last 11 Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, including each of their last four in a row – their longest ever league losing run to Spurs. Tottenham have won both of their last two league visits to Elland Road and could beat Leeds United away from home three times running in the league for the very first time.

title: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Lille have won just one of their last 13 home Ligue 1 games against Paris SG, a 5-1 victory on 14 April 2019, which remains Paris Saint-Germain's biggest away defeat in the top-flight in the 21st century. Lille have lost their last two Ligue 1 matches and could suffer three consecutive defeats in the competition for the first time since December 2019-January 2020. Lille could also fail to score in three consecutive Ligue 1 games for the first time since September 2017.

title: History of the Asian Games
synopsis: From its beginnings to today, the Asian Games torch lighting has become a dazzling showcase of creativity and technology. Each edition brings fresh innovation, with Doha 2006’s unforgettable horse-and-rider moment still hailed as a highlight. As the 2026 Games in Japan draw near, excitement builds over what new spectacle will capture the world’s imagination.

title: Sevilla vs Barcelona - Spanish LaLiga 2025/26 - Week 8 - Mini Match

synopsis: Sevilla have not won any of their last 19 LaLiga games against Barcelona, a run that stretches back to October 2015, losing their last seven in a row – their longest consecutive losing streak against the Catalans in the top-flight. title: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7 - Mini Match
title_en_trans: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7 - Mini Match
synopsis: Lille have won just one of their last 13 home Ligue 1 games against Paris SG, a 5-1 victory on 14 April 2019, which remains Paris Saint-Germain's biggest away defeat in the top-flight in the 21st century. Lille have lost their last two Ligue 1 matches and could suffer three consecutive defeats in the competition for the first time since December 2019-January 2020. Lille could also fail to score in three consecutive Ligue 1 games for the first time since September 2017.

title: Al Hilal SFC (KSA) vs Al Duhail SC (QAT) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
title_en_trans: Al Hilal SFC (KSA) vs Al Duhail SC (QAT) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
synopsis: Al Duhail won their first AFC Champions League Elite meeting with Al-Hilal, but Al-Hilal are unbeaten in the six since, including their joint-biggest win in the competition  – Al Duhail’s heaviest defeat in the tournament. Qatari teams have lost their last five matches against Saudi sides in the competition; their last win was Al Sadd’s 2-1 victory over Al-Nassr in December 2014. Qatari teams have lost more matches  and conceded more goals  against Saudi teams than against any other nation.

title: Istres vs Montpellier - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Istres vs Montpellier - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Sevilla vs Barcelona - Spanish LaLiga 2025/26 - Week 8 - Mini Match
title_en_trans: Sevilla vs Barcelona - Spanish LaLiga 2025/26 - Week 8 - Mini Match
synopsis: Sevilla have not won any of their last 19 LaLiga games against Barcelona, a run that stretches back to October 2015, losing their last seven in a row – their longest consecutive losing streak against the Catalans in the top-flight. Barcelona have avoided defeat in their last nine away LaLiga matches against Sevilla, their longest unbeaten run away to them in the competition.

title: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Everton vs Crystal Palace - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Everton vs Crystal Palace - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Everton have lost just one of their last 21 Premier League meetings with Crystal Palace, a 1-3 defeat in December 2021. Indeed, among all sides they have faced 20+ times in the competition, their points-per-game rate of 1.81 against the Eagles is bettered only against West Brom. Crystal Palace are winless in each of their last 10 Premier League away games against Everton  since a 3-2 victory in September 2014 under Neil Warnock.

synopsis: This will be the first fixture in AFC Champions League Elite between Nasaf and Al-Hilal, Nasaf have won just one of their eight games against teams from Saudi Arabia in the competition  and are winless in their last four such games. Al-Hilal have lost just one of their 14 group stage games against teams from Uzbekistan in AFC Champions League Elite history, a 1-2 loss to FK Mash’al Mubarek in 2006; they have scored in each of their 14 such games in the competition, scoring at least twice in 11 of these.

title_en_trans: Al Gharafa SC (QAT) vs Al Shorta (IRQ) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD2
synopsis: This will be the first meeting between Al Gharafa and Al Shorta in the AFC Champions League Elite; Al Gharafa is winless in their two encounters against Iraqi sides in the competition  while Al Shorta is unbeaten in their last two games against Qatari sides. Al Gharafa won their most recent home game in the AFC Champions League Elite, the last time they won back-to-back home games in the competition was a run of three games between May 2012 and April 2013; they kept a clean sheet in their previous home game, they have never recorded back-to-back clean sheets at home in the competition.

title: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs. Liverpool - English Premier League 2025/2026
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

synopsis: Le Havre have lost four of their last five home games against Rennes in Ligue 1, after only losing one of the first 16. Le Havre failed to score for the third time in Ligue 1 in 2025 in their last match at Metz ; only Lyon  and Paris SG  have failed to score in fewer matches in the competition this calendar year among ever present teams. It was also Le Havre’s second clean sheet of the year, the lowest tally amongst all teams in Ligue 1.

title: My Faith in Sport
synopsis: Ramadan is a crucial period in the Islamic calendar but fasting (Sawm) can provide complications for athletes who are trying to compete at the highest level. But to what extent is fasting a negative or can it actually aid performance? We look at the life and adaptation throughout Ramadan of Adam Azim – an unbeaten professional boxer from the UK, Fares El Bakh – a weightlifter who won Qatar’s first ever Olympic gold medal, and Zainab Alema – a rugby player who is aiming to become the first player to represent England wearing a hijab.Experts in Sports Science and Nutrition from Aspetar Clinic, Qatar also add detail of the physical impact athletes encounter during Ramadan

synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: My Faith in Sport - Salah
synopsis: Exploring the importance of prayer within Islam, the episode begins with an overview of our seven athletes as they introduce themselves and why Islam is so important to them. We are also introduced to Omar Sulieman, a notable Imam, who acts as narration throughout the series and a guiding voice on the key principles of Islam. The life and career of Sofyan Amrabat is explored, showcasing his role as a key part of the Fenerbahce team in Turkey and the Moroccan national side. The Atlas Lions’ run to the semi-finals of the FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022 is explored, with the impact that Salah played in the team’s belief and positivity throughout the tournament.

synopsis: Olympique Lyonnais are unbeaten in their last 17 Ligue 1 matches against Toulouse FC, a longer run in the top-flight has only been recorded against Saint-Étienne. title: Istres vs Montpellier - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Istres vs Montpellier - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title_en_trans: Tractor FC (IRN) vs Al Wahda FC (UAE) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD2
synopsis: This will be the first ever AFC Champions League Elite fixture between Tractor and Al Wahda; Tractor are unbeaten in home games against sides from UAE in the competition, while Al Wahda are winless in away matches against sides from Iran in the tournament. Al Wahda won their opening game of an AFC Champions League Elite campaign for the first time since 2007, beating Al-Ittihad 2-1 on the opening matchday of the 2025-26 season; the only other time they won their first two matches of an AFC Champions League Elite campaign was also in 2007.

title_en_trans: Monaco vs Nice - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Monaco will face OGC Nice for the 131st time in all competitions. Monaco have recorded 58 wins against OGC Nice, a figure they have only achieved against Lyon and Rennes. OGC Nice, in turn, have lost to Monaco 58 times in all competitions, with only defeats against Marseille  being more frequent. Monaco have lost three of their last five Ligue 1 matches against Nice, as many defeats as in their previous 12 encounters with OGCN.

title: My Faith in Sport
synopsis: Ramadan is a crucial period in the Islamic calendar but fasting (Sawm) can provide complications for athletes who are trying to compete at the highest level. But to what extent is fasting a negative or can it actually aid performance? We look at the life and adaptation throughout Ramadan of Adam Azim – an unbeaten professional boxer from the UK, Fares El Bakh – a weightlifter who won Qatar’s first ever Olympic gold medal, and Zainab Alema – a rugby player who is aiming to become the first player to represent England wearing a hijab.Experts in Sports Science and Nutrition from Aspetar Clinic, Qatar also add detail of the physical impact athletes encounter during Ramadan
synopsis_en_trans: Ramadan is a crucial period in the Islamic calendar but fasting (Sawm) can provide complications for athletes who are trying to compete at the highest level. But to what extent is fasting a negative or can it actually aid performance? We look at the life and adaptation throughout Ramadan of Adam Azim – an unbeaten professional boxer from the UK, Fares El Bakh – a weightlifter who won Qatar’s first ever Olympic gold medal, and Zainab Alema – a rugby player who is aiming to become the first player to represent England wearing a hijab.Experts in Sports Science and Nutrition from Aspetar Clinic, Qatar also add detail of the physical impact athletes encounter during Ramadan

synopsis: Chengdu Rongcheng will face Gangwon for the first time in AFC Champions League Elite; each of the last three games in the competition between teams from Korea and China have been won by the former by an exact 2-1 score, including Gangwon’s win over Shanghai Shenhua in the first round of the 2025-26 season. Gangwon beat Shanghai Shenhua 2-1 in their first ever AFC Champions League Elite game at home; the last Korean side to suffer at least one defeat in their first two games in the competition is Jeju United in 2011, while no side from Korea has suffered defeat in their first away game in the AFC Champions League Elite.

synopsis: Johor Darul Ta’zim will be playing against Machida Zelvia for the first time in AFC Champions League history; Johor Darul Ta’zim are winless in their last seven games in the competition against teams from Japan, failing to score in each of the last five of these games. title: Le Havre vs Rennes - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Le Havre vs Rennes - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Le Havre have lost four of their last five home games against Rennes in Ligue 1, after only losing one of the first 16. Le Havre failed to score for the third time in Ligue 1 in 2025 in their last match at Metz ; only Lyon  and Paris SG  have failed to score in fewer matches in the competition this calendar year among ever present teams. It was also Le Havre’s second clean sheet of the year, the lowest tally amongst all teams in Ligue 1.

title: My Faith in Sport - Ummah
synopsis:
Ummah is an Arabic word meaning "community” – an important concept in Islam as it encourages Muslims to support and help each other especially in times of need. Zakat is one of the most important aspects in Islam - it is the principle of giving back to a community/person that needs it more than you. 
This episode will look into Zakat around footballers Ali-Al Hamadi and Nadia Nadim and the role it plays in their lives. Al-Hamadi is the first Iraqi to play in the Premier League with a remarkable back story – his family escaped persecution in their homeland in the early 2000s before settling, as refugees, in Liverpool. title: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

synopsis:
The AFC Champions League Two is the second-tier competition of Asian club football, ranked below the AFC Champions League Elite. 
Participation in the competition is open to clubs from the top 12 nations in the East and the West region based on the AFC club competitions ranking.
All games are live and exclusive only on beIN.

synopsis: This will be the first ever AFC Champions League Elite fixture between Tractor and Al Wahda; Tractor are unbeaten in home games against sides from UAE in the competition, while Al Wahda are winless in away matches against sides from Iran in the tournament. title: Delfina Brea Senesi (ARG) / Gemma Triay Pons (ESP) vs  Ariana Sanchez Fallada (ESP) / Paula Josemari
title_en_trans: Delfina Brea Senesi (ARG) / Gemma Triay Pons (ESP) vs  Ariana Sanchez Fallada (ESP) / Paula Josemari
synopsis: World No.1 pairing Gemma Triay/Delfina Brea face No.2 Ariana Sánchez/Paula Josemaría at Rotterdam Ahoy. A classic rivalry: Triay/Brea lead the season with multiple titles, including Germany P2 last week, while Sánchez/Josemaría chase revenge after losing six of seven meetings this year. Expect sharp returns, low volleys, and golden-point pressure in a battle for supremacy.

title: Paris FC vs Lorient - Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Paris FC vs Lorient - Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Paris FC beat Lorient 3-2 in March 2025  after failing to win any of their first seven meetings in all competitions against them this century. Paris FC have conceded 13 goals in their six Ligue 1 matches this season, with only Lorient  conceding more; this is as many goals as Paris FC conceded in their final 12 Ligue 2 games last season.

title: Saint-Raphaël vs Toulouse - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Saint-Raphaël vs Toulouse - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Chelsea vs Benfica - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Benfica - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
synopsis: Chelsea have won all four of their competitive meetings with Benfica, with the most recent of those coming earlier this year at the FIFA Club World Cup. This will be the first meeting between Chelsea and Benfica in the group/league phase of a competition, with the previous four all having come in the knockout stages: UEFA Champions League quarter-finals in 2011-12, UEFA Europa League final in 2012-13 and the FIFA Club World Cup last 16 earlier this year.

Indeed, among all sides they have faced 20+ times in the competition, their points-per-game rate of 1.81 against the Eagles is bettered only against West Brom. Crystal Palace are winless in each of their last 10 Premier League away games against Everton  since a 3-2 victory in September 2014 under Neil Warnock.

title: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

As the 2026 Games in Japan draw near, excitement builds over what new spectacle will capture the world’s imagination.

synopsis: This will be the first AFC Champions League Elite fixture between Vissel Kobe and Melbourne City; City are without a win in any of their three Champions League Elite games against Japanese sides, while Kobe have won their only previous game against an Australian opposition in the competition. Vissel Kobe won their last AFC Champions League Elite game against Shanghai Port by a 3-0 margin; however, they have not won consecutive games in the competition since their three-match winning run between October and November 2024.

synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

synopsis: Ulsan HD have won each of their three AFC Champions League Elite games against Shanghai Shenhua, scoring at least two goals in each of those games; in fact, they have won seven of their last eight such fixtures against Chinese teams, with their only defeat in that period being a 1-3 loss to Shanghai Port on 26 November 2024. title_en_trans: Monaco vs Nice - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Monaco will face OGC Nice for the 131st time in all competitions. Monaco have recorded 58 wins against OGC Nice, a figure they have only achieved against Lyon and Rennes. OGC Nice, in turn, have lost to Monaco 58 times in all competitions, with only defeats against Marseille  being more frequent. Monaco have lost three of their last five Ligue 1 matches against Nice, as many defeats as in their previous 12 encounters with OGCN.

title: My Faith in Sport - Sawm
synopsis: Ramadan is a crucial period in the Islamic calendar but fasting (Sawm) can provide complications for athletes who are trying to compete at the highest level. But to what extent is fasting a negative or can it actually aid performance? We look at the life and adaptation throughout Ramadan of Adam Azim – an unbeaten professional boxer from the UK, Fares El Bakh – a weightlifter who won Qatar’s first ever Olympic gold medal, and Zainab Alema – a rugby player who is aiming to become the first player to represent England wearing a hijab. Experts in Sports Science and Nutrition from Aspetar Clinic, Qatar also add detail of the physical impact athletes encounter during Ramadan.

The most famous participating clubs are Al-Sadd, the champions of the last season; Al-Rayyan and Al-Arabi, the popular teams, Al-Duhail and Al-Gharafa, serious contenders for the title every season. title: Arturo Coello (ESP) / Agustin Tapia (ARG) vs  Federico Chingotto (ARG) / Alejandro Galan (ESP) - Men

synopsis: Top seeds Arturo Coello/Agustín Tapia clash with No.2 Alejandro Galán/Federico Chingotto. Coello/Tapia dominated most of 2025, but Galán/Chingotto struck back with victory in Germany P2. synopsis: Aston Villa have won both of their last two Premier League games against Burnley but haven’t won more successive league meetings with the Clarets since March 1900. Burnley’s last league visit to Aston Villa saw them lose 3-2 in December 2023; they last lost successive away league matches at Villa in April 1966.

title: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue

synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

title: Delfina Brea Senesi (ARG) / Gemma Triay Pons (ESP) vs  Ariana Sanchez Fallada (ESP) / Paula Josemari
title_en_trans: Delfina Brea Senesi (ARG) / Gemma Triay Pons (ESP) vs  Ariana Sanchez Fallada (ESP) / Paula Josemari
synopsis: World No.1 pairing Gemma Triay/Delfina Brea face No.2 Ariana Sánchez/Paula Josemaría at Rotterdam Ahoy. A classic rivalry: Triay/Brea lead the season with multiple titles, including Germany P2 last week, while Sánchez/Josemaría chase revenge after losing six of seven meetings this year. Expect sharp returns, low volleys, and golden-point pressure in a battle for supremacy.

synopsis: Le Havre have lost four of their last five home games against Rennes in Ligue 1, after only losing one of the first 16. Le Havre failed to score for the third time in Ligue 1 in 2025 in their last match at Metz ; only Lyon  and Paris SG  have failed to score in fewer matches in the competition this calendar year among ever present teams. It was also Le Havre’s second clean sheet of the year, the lowest tally amongst all teams in Ligue 1.

synopsis: This will be the first meeting between Al-Ittihad and Shabab Al Ahli in AFC Champions League Elite history; teams from Saudi Arabia have won seven of their last eight games in the competition against teams from UAE, however, the one loss in this run was Al-Ittihad’s 1-2 loss to Al Wahda in their opening matchday of the 2025-26 season. Al-Ittihad have lost each of their last three AFC Champions League Elite games, their joint-longest run of such games in the competition, including a 1-2 loss to Al Wahda on Matchday 1; Al-Ittihad have never lost each of their first two games of an AFC Champions League Elite campaign and only twice have they failed to win any of their first two games.

synopsis: World No.1 pairing Gemma Triay/Delfina Brea face No.2 Ariana Sánchez/Paula Josemaría at Rotterdam Ahoy. A classic rivalry: Triay/Brea lead the season with multiple titles, including Germany P2 last week, while Sánchez/Josemaría chase revenge after losing six of seven meetings this year. Expect sharp returns, low volleys, and golden-point pressure in a battle for supremacy.

synopsis: Lille have won just one of their last 13 home Ligue 1 games against Paris SG, a 5-1 victory on 14 April 2019, which remains Paris Saint-Germain's biggest away defeat in the top-flight in the 21st century. Lille have lost their last two Ligue 1 matches and could suffer three consecutive defeats in the competition for the first time since December 2019-January 2020. Lille could also fail to score in three consecutive Ligue 1 games for the first time since September 2017.

title: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Lille vs PSG - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Lille have won just one of their last 13 home Ligue 1 games against Paris SG, a 5-1 victory on 14 April 2019, which remains Paris Saint-Germain's biggest away defeat in the top-flight in the 21st century. Lille have lost their last two Ligue 1 matches and could suffer three consecutive defeats in the competition for the first time since December 2019-January 2020. Lille could also fail to score in three consecutive Ligue 1 games for the first time since September 2017.

title: My Faith in Sport - Salah
synopsis: Exploring the importance of prayer within Islam, the episode begins with an overview of our seven athletes as they introduce themselves and why Islam is so important to them. We are also introduced to Omar Sulieman, a notable Imam, who acts as narration throughout the series and a guiding voice on the key principles of Islam. The life and career of Sofyan Amrabat is explored, showcasing his role as a key part of the Fenerbahce team in Turkey and the Moroccan national side. The Atlas Lions’ run to the semi-finals of the FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022 is explored, with the impact that Salah played in the team’s belief and positivity throughout the tournament.

title: Chelsea vs Benfica - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Benfica - UEFA Champions League 2025/26 - MD2
synopsis: Chelsea have won all four of their competitive meetings with Benfica, with the most recent of those coming earlier this year at the FIFA Club World Cup. This will be the first meeting between Chelsea and Benfica in the group/league phase of a competition, with the previous four all having come in the knockout stages: UEFA Champions League quarter-finals in 2011-12, UEFA Europa League final in 2012-13 and the FIFA Club World Cup last 16 earlier this year.

title: Delfina Brea Senesi (ARG) / Gemma Triay Pons (ESP) vs  Ariana Sanchez Fallada (ESP) / Paula Josemari
title_en_trans: Delfina Brea Senesi (ARG) / Gemma Triay Pons (ESP) vs  Ariana Sanchez Fallada (ESP) / Paula Josemari
synopsis: World No.1 pairing Gemma Triay/Delfina Brea face No.2 Ariana Sánchez/Paula Josemaría at Rotterdam Ahoy. A classic rivalry: Triay/Brea lead the season with multiple titles, including Germany P2 last week, while Sánchez/Josemaría chase revenge after losing six of seven meetings this year. Expect sharp returns, low volleys, and golden-point pressure in a battle for supremacy.

title: My Faith in Sport - Taffakur
synopsis: Islam teaches Muslims about ‘Tawakkul’ meaning trusting in God’s plan. Muslims believe in the idea that with anything in life we put forward our best efforts but ultimately the rest is left to God and believing whatever the outcome, it was pre-written. Omar Marmoush is the feature athlete in the final episode of the series – from the outskirts of the Eintracht Frankfurt side to an $80m move to Premier League Manchester City, his last 18 months has seen an incredible rise. His love of Ramadan and belief that fasting elevates his game is a central theme of the final episode alongside detail of his early life, career and his unfaltering belief in Islam. The series concludes with all athletes re

title: Melbourne City FC (AUS) vs Sanfrecce Hiroshima (JPN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East M
title_en_trans: Melbourne City FC (AUS) vs Sanfrecce Hiroshima (JPN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East M
synopsis: This will be the first-ever AFC Champions League Elite meeting between Melbourne City and Sanfrecce Hiroshima; City are winless in each of their two games against Japanese opposition in the competition, while a win for Sanfrecce would see them beat Australian opponents in three consecutive games for the first time in competition history. Melbourne City are winless in each of their last three matches in the AFC Champions League Elite, their longest such run in the competition; in fact, they have begun each of their previous two campaigns in the competition with draws.

Melbourne City are winless in each of their last three matches in the AFC Champions League Elite, their longest such run in the competition; in fact, they have begun each of their previous two campaigns in the competition with draws.

synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: Gangwon FC (KOR) vs Shanghai Shenhua FC (CHN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD1
title_en_trans: Gangwon FC (KOR) vs Shanghai Shenhua FC (CHN) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD1
synopsis: This will be the first AFC Champions League Elite meeting between Gangwon and Shanghai Shenhua, with the former set to play their first-ever game in the competition; Shenhua have lost each of their last two matches against South Korean opposition in the Champions League Elite, another defeat here will see them equal their longest such run in competition history. Shanghai Shenhua lost their most recent AFC Champions League Elite match 0-4 to Kawasaki Frontale on 12 March 2025; failure to score against Gangwon will see them go scoreless in consecutive games for the first time in the competition since May 2011.

synopsis: Chelsea have won all four of their competitive meetings with Benfica, with the most recent of those coming earlier this year at the FIFA Club World Cup. This will be the first meeting between Chelsea and Benfica in the group/league phase of a competition, with the previous four all having come in the knockout stages: UEFA Champions League quarter-finals in 2011-12, UEFA Europa League final in 2012-13 and the FIFA Club World Cup last 16 earlier this year.

synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

synopsis: FC Seoul are unbeaten in each of their four meetings against Buriram United in the AFC Champions League Elite, including wins in each of their last two; in fact, FC Seoul have lost just one of their six meetings against Thai sides in the competition, with the loss coming in their most recent such game. title: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3

synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

synopsis: The 2025/2026 UEFA Women's Champions League is live and exclusive only on beIN. title_en_trans: Qatar vs UAE - AFC Asian Qualifiers Road To 26 Playoffs - MD3
synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

title: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8

synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Chelsea vs Liverpool -English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: After their 3-1 win in May, Chelsea could enjoy back-to-back league wins over Liverpool for the first time since November 2014. Liverpool are winless in their last four Premier League games at Stamford Bridge  and could lose away to Chelsea two seasons running in the league for the first time since losing three on the bounce from 2004-05 to 2006-07.

title: FC Machida Zelvia (JPN) vs FC Seoul (KOR)- AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD1
title_en_trans: FC Machida Zelvia (JPN) vs FC Seoul (KOR)- AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - East MD1
synopsis: This will be the first ever AFC Champions League Elite meeting between Machida Zelvia and FC Seoul, with the former playing in the competition for the first time ever; four J1 teams have previously played their first ever AFC Champions League Elite game against K-League clubs and won two  with each of those matches having mutiple goals. FC Seoul have scored in each of their last 11 AFC Champions League Elite matches; in fact, they have scored on the opening matchday in six of their previous eight participations in the competition, failing to do so in only 2015 and 2017.

title: Olympique Lyonnais vs Toulouse - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
title_en_trans: Olympique Lyonnais vs Toulouse - French Ligue 1 2025/2026 Week 7
synopsis: Olympique Lyonnais are unbeaten in their last 17 Ligue 1 matches against Toulouse FC, a longer run in the top-flight has only been recorded against Saint-Étienne. title: My Faith in Sport - Ummah
synopsis:
Ummah is an Arabic word meaning "community” – an important concept in Islam as it encourages Muslims to support and help each other especially in times of need. Zakat is one of the most important aspects in Islam - it is the principle of giving back to a community/person that needs it more than you. 
This episode will look into Zakat around footballers Ali-Al Hamadi and Nadia Nadim and the role it plays in their lives. Al-Hamadi is the first Iraqi to play in the Premier League with a remarkable back story – his family escaped persecution in their homeland in the early 2000s before settling, as refugees, in Liverpool. synopsis:
The fourth round of AFC 2026 FIFA World Cup Qualification matches take place over three days.
The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.
Group B Features KSA, Iraq & Indonesia who will play their games in KSA.
The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.

synopsis: The 2025–26 UEFA Europa League is the secondary club football tournament organised by UEFA. This is the second season played under a new format, which replaced the 32-team group stage with a 36-team league phase. Tottenham Hotspur are the reigning champions. The final will be played on 20 May 2026 at Beşiktaş Stadium in Istanbul, Turkey.

title: Al Ahli Saudi FC (KSA) vs PFC Nasaf (UZB) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
title_en_trans: Al Ahli Saudi FC (KSA) vs PFC Nasaf (UZB) - AFC Champions League Elite 2025/2026 - West MD1
synopsis: This will be the fifth AFC Champions League Elite meeting between Al-Ahli and Nasaf, with Nasaf’s only win coming in their most recent such game on 2 March 2016 ; Al-Ahli’s most recent game in the competition against Uzbek opposition was a 2-1 win over Pakhtakor Tashkent on 20 May 2019, a win here will see them win two consecutive such games for the first time in competition history. Al-Ahli are unbeaten in each of their last 18 AFC Champions League Elite games, including the final of the 2024-25 edition ; avoiding defeat here will see them equal Gamba Osaka for the joint third-longest such run in the competition.

title: Everton vs Crystal Palace - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
title_en_trans: Everton vs Crystal Palace - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
synopsis: Everton have lost just one of their last 21 Premier League meetings with Crystal Palace, a 1-3 defeat in December 2021. Indeed, among all sides they have faced 20+ times in the competition, their points-per-game rate of 1.81 against the Eagles is bettered only against West Brom. Crystal Palace are winless in each of their last 10 Premier League away games against Everton  since a 3-2 victory in September 2014 under Neil Warnock.

title: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
title_en_trans: Nîmes vs Nantes - LNH Division 1 - French Handball Starligue
synopsis: Dive into the excitement of French handball with Liqui Moly Starligue, formerly LNH Division 1. Established in 1952, this premier league event features 16 top teams battling for glory. With Montpellier’s  14 Handball titles and Paris Saint-Germain's 11 wins, the competition is fierce. Champions earn spots in the EHF Champions League, while cup winners qualify for the European League.

synopsis: This will be the first ever AFC Champions League Elite meeting between Al Shorta and Al Sadd; Iraqi teams have won five of their last seven matches against Qatari sides in the competition, after winning just one of the first seven. title: Longines Global Champions Tour 2025 - Rome

The third-placed and fourth-placed teams from the third round were divided into two groups of three teams.
Group A features Qatar, UAE & Oman and will play their matches in Qatar.

The winners of each group will qualify directly for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, while the runners-up will advance to the fifth round.
